00:01:15.280 --> 00:01:18.380
In life, everybody is
struggling with something.

00:01:18.380 --> 00:01:20.137
Whether it's within
your own mind

00:01:20.137 --> 00:01:21.720
or whether it's
external to your mind.

00:01:21.720 --> 00:01:26.290
It's somebody in your family, a
sickness, a death, an illness,

00:01:26.290 --> 00:01:31.240
stress, worry, mental
anxiety, and so on, we all

00:01:31.240 --> 00:01:33.220
have something to worry about.

00:01:33.220 --> 00:01:35.950
And they are all
equally the same.

00:01:35.950 --> 00:01:39.700
There is nothing stronger or
worse than anybody else's pain

00:01:39.700 --> 00:01:42.760
or issues that they have.

00:01:42.760 --> 00:01:45.310
So my whole talk,
really, is about family.

00:01:45.310 --> 00:01:48.150
And there was two things I
was thinking of last night

00:01:48.150 --> 00:01:50.247
that I'd like to start off.

00:01:50.247 --> 00:01:51.580
I'm going to do a little survey.

00:01:51.580 --> 00:01:54.769
Now, you can put up your
hand or not, whichever you're

00:01:54.769 --> 00:01:55.810
feeling comfortable with.

00:01:55.810 --> 00:02:00.340
But hopefully, you'll just
bear with me for a second.

00:02:00.340 --> 00:02:04.420
So everybody here is
working in Google.

00:02:04.420 --> 00:02:11.280
So my first question is when
you were in school and college,

00:02:11.280 --> 00:02:14.080
was Google going to be your
number one place to work?

00:02:14.080 --> 00:02:16.455
When you were in college, you
said, right, I'm in school.

00:02:16.455 --> 00:02:17.954
I'm going to leave
school, I'm going

00:02:17.954 --> 00:02:20.020
to go to college because
I want to be in Google.

00:02:20.020 --> 00:02:23.350
Hands up who had that
thought in their mindset

00:02:23.350 --> 00:02:26.430
when they were studying.

00:02:26.430 --> 00:02:27.040
Good.

00:02:27.040 --> 00:02:27.539
Good.

00:02:27.539 --> 00:02:28.090
[LAUGHTER]

00:02:28.090 --> 00:02:29.540
Great.

00:02:29.540 --> 00:02:30.190
We had one.

00:02:30.190 --> 00:02:32.510
OK, he's a real Googler.

00:02:32.510 --> 00:02:35.890
He watched that movie we all
watched, and we loved it.

00:02:35.890 --> 00:02:36.660
OK.

00:02:36.660 --> 00:02:38.470
So that's good.

00:02:38.470 --> 00:02:43.540
Now, how many of you now have
a qualification or a training

00:02:43.540 --> 00:02:46.590
relative to working in Google?

00:02:46.590 --> 00:02:50.880
So I presume most of you would
have some sort of qualification

00:02:50.880 --> 00:02:52.300
or degree or whatever.

00:02:52.300 --> 00:02:55.800
So a lot of you have trained
to do a job that you never

00:02:55.800 --> 00:02:58.080
really thought that
you would be doing.

00:02:58.080 --> 00:03:00.820
Now, bear with me for a second.

00:03:00.820 --> 00:03:04.560
The other side of
this little equation--

00:03:04.560 --> 00:03:08.390
hands up here, anybody
who have children.

00:03:08.390 --> 00:03:08.890
OK.

00:03:08.890 --> 00:03:11.180
So there's is a good
few who have children.

00:03:11.180 --> 00:03:13.700
Anybody-- you don't
have to answer this--

00:03:13.700 --> 00:03:18.020
anybody here in a relationship
that hope maybe one

00:03:18.020 --> 00:03:20.570
day they will have a family?

00:03:20.570 --> 00:03:22.520
OK.

00:03:22.520 --> 00:03:25.740
Now, finally, anybody who
hasn't put their hand up,

00:03:25.740 --> 00:03:30.532
is anybody here who was ever in
school when they were younger--

00:03:30.532 --> 00:03:32.490
oh, when I grow up, I'm
going to have a family,

00:03:32.490 --> 00:03:34.110
and get married, and have kids.

00:03:34.110 --> 00:03:36.840
Does that cover the
rest of you here?

00:03:36.840 --> 00:03:38.650
OK.

